REFERRAL_HIST.name: REFERRAL_HIST
REFERRAL_HIST.description: The REFERRAL_HIST table contains information on changes to referrals stored in system.

columns.name: REFERRAL_ID
columns.description: The referral ID for the referral record.

columns.name: LINE
columns.description: The line number of the change to the referral. For example, if the referral is changed twice, the first change will have a line value of 1, while the second change will have a line value of 2.

columns.name: CHANGE_DATE
columns.description: The date of the change to the referral.

columns.name: CHANGE_TYPE_C_NAME
columns.description: The category value indicating the type of referral change.
entries: Confirmation Expired - Canceled by Nightly Processing
Change Request to Upgrade to Cancer Pathway
Canceled Order - Referral Status Not Changed
Change Primary Referral Diagnosis Add Codes
Use Service-Level Authorization Count in Claim
Remove Service-Level Authorization Count from Claim
Change Reporting Referred To Is Contracted Override
Change Reporting Referred By Is Contracted Override
Financial Commitment Free Text Service Provider Name
Financial Commitment Free Text Service Provider Address
Change Concurrent Review Next Review Due
ANSI 278 Inquiry Message Failed to Send
UM Turnaround Time Start Ignore Instant
UM Turnaround Time End Ignore Instant
Authorization Status Set to No Auth Required

columns.name: CHANGE_USER_ID
columns.description: The ID number of the user who made the change to the referral.

columns.name: CHANGE_USER_ID_NAME
columns.description: The name of the user record. This name may be hidden.

columns.name: PREVIOUS_VALUE
columns.description: Some of the information on the referral is tracked when it changes. This stores the previous value of an item if it is tracked when it changes.

columns.name: CHANGE_DATETIME
columns.description: The date and time of the change to the referral.

columns.name: AUTH_HX_EVENT_NO
columns.description: The event no of the authorization history

columns.name: AUTH_HX_NOTE_ID
columns.description: Referral audit trail item to store note Id

columns.name: CHANGE_LOCAL_DTTM
columns.description: The authorization date and time as an instant in the local time zone

columns.name: NEW_RFL_STATUS_C_NAME
columns.description: If the item being changed is Referral Status (I RFL 50), this item stores the new value for that item.

columns.name: NEW_PEND_RSN_C_NAME
columns.description: If the item being changed is Reason Pending (I RFL 18003), this item stores the new value for that item.
